comments: Allen (PHX) places his hand on Clarkson's (UTA) side and marginal contact occurs as the two engage and disengage during the screen.
Clarkson (UTA) avoids placing part of his hand underneath the ball along the sideline.
Durant (PHX) leans to his left as he establishes position in Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal leg contact occurs with Clarkson splits the defenders at the end of the drive.
Allen (PHX) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Clarkson (UTA) after the release.
Allen (PHX) makes contact with the ball after it touches the backboard and has a chance to score.
George (UTA) extends his arm and marginal contact occurs with Durant's (PHX) wrist as he attempts to get to the pass.
Booker (PHX) moves his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
George (UTA) brings his arm toward Booker's (PHX) path and marginal body contact occurs as the two come together during the drive.
Nurkic (PHX) is in the lane for at or about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Markkanen (UTA) brings his hands toward Allen (PHX) and marginal contact occurs as Markkanen releases away to roll.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Collins (UTA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Booker (PHX) touches the ball last before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Jazz.
Bates-Diop (PHX) moves into George's (UTA) path and delivers contact that dislodges George from his rebounding position.
Durant (PHX) contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt and makes clean contact with the ball prior to any incidental contact.
Agbaji (UTA) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Booker (PHX) is drawn into the air by the pump fake and initiates illegal body contact with Collins (UTA) that affects his SQBR.
Allen (PHX) lowers his arm and avoids making contact on Clarkson's (UTA) arm during his upward shooting motion. As Allen contests, marginal "high-five" contact occurs with Clarkson upon the release.
George (UTA) steps out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
Gordon (PHX) engages and disengages with Markkanen (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Allen (PHX) and Markkanen (UTA) mutually engage and disengage with one another off-ball as Markkenen rolls to the basket.
Gordon (PHX) makes contact to George's (UTA) body while defending the drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Gordon (PHX) jumps into Clarkson's (UTA) body and initiates illegal contact which affects his driving shot attempt.
Clarkson (UTA) and Durant (PHX) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Bates-Diop (PHX) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Clarkson (UTA) moves and extends his arm outside the frame of his body and illegal contact occurs that affects Okogie's (PHX) ability to defend over the screen.
Okogie (PHX) steps into Markkanen's (UTA) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Agbaji (UTA) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
Clarkson (UTA) commits a take foul on Gordon (PHX).
Allen (PHX) moves alongside George's (UTA) path with a collapsed forearm and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) brings both hands forward as he moves alongside Markkanen's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs at the start of Markkanen's drive.
Nurkic (PHX) is in the lane for at or about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Correctly called PHX shot clock violation.
Markkanen (UTA) slightly re-establishes his screening position in Allen's (PHX) path and marginal contact occurs with Allen as the screen is set.
Clarkson (UTA) gathers the pass on two feet and legally establishes his left foot as his pivot.
Durant (PHX) extends both hands forward and initiates contact with Markkanen (UTA), which affects Markkanen's FOM off-ball.
George (UTA) takes longer than five seconds to inbound the ball.
George (UTA) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).

Replay review of the foul called on Durant (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Durant was deemed to clearly and conclusively make contact with the ball, deflecting Markkanen's (UTA) shot. His contact to Markkanen's hand after the ball trajectory was affected was incidental. Replay was also used to confirm that the contact created by Markkanen when he kicked his leg out toward Durant was both marginal and that it occurred after the point of interruption, with no time remaining on the clock.
